                <componentInstanceProperties>
                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Individual relationships&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt; are recorded in the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Contact Contact Relationship&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt; object and their roles are defined by &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Party Role Relationship&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt; records in your system. Below is a list of common &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Party Role Relationships&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt; that you can select and create. To create a role not displayed below, manually create one by going to the Party Role Relationship tab at the top of this screen and click “New.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</value>
